ExecDesc.value: Apple Computer Finder DMG Volume Name Memory Corruption

EngDesc.value: There exists a memory corruption vulnerability in the Apple Finder product. The flaw is due to improper bounds checking on the length of the Volume name in the DMG disk images. An attacker may exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to open a crafted DMG disk image. Exploitation of the vulnerability may result in injection and execution of arbitrary code within the security context of the target user.
